<task id="015" project="spaarke-datagrid-framework-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BffDataverseClient implementation using @spaarke/auth.authenticatedFetch</title>
    <phase>2: Phase B — BFF Passthrough</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>011,012,013,014</dependencies>
    <blocks>017,023,024,041,052</blocks>
    <tags>fluent-ui, frontend, typescript, dataverse, auth</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Code implementation of IDataverseClient contract; ADR-028 binding; consumer-facing API</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Depends on all 4 endpoint tasks completing — serial integration point</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `BffDataverseClient` in `@spaarke/ui-components/services/BffDataverseClient.ts`. Same 5-method `IDataverseClient` contract as `XrmDataverseClient`. Uses `@spaarke/auth.authenticatedFetch` for ALL HTTP calls (no direct `fetch`). Configurable `bffBaseUrl`. R1 is READ-ONLY: writes throw `BffDataverseClient.WritesNotSupportedError`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in `@spaarke/auth.authenticatedFetch`, ADR-028 Spaarke Auth, and async TypeScript clients.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `BffDataverseClient` implements `IDataverseClient` interface; routes all 5 methods to the corresponding BFF endpoints (011-014); uses `authenticatedFetch`; ProblemDetails responses unwrapped to typed errors; consumer can swap `XrmDataverseClient` ↔ `BffDataverseClient` without code change.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-BFF-06. The framework's `<DataGrid />` accepts `dataverseClient` prop; defaults to `XrmDataverseClient` (MDA host). Custom Page hosts and workspace widgets can pass `new BffDataverseClient({ bffBaseUrl })` instead. Both impls satisfy the same `IDataverseClient` contract from task 001. R1 BffDataverseClient is READ-ONLY — there's no write endpoint yet; calling write methods throws a clear error so devs know to use Xrm impl for writes.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/BffDataverseClient.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/IDataverseClient.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/tests/services/BffDataverseClient.test.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/@spaarke/auth/src/authenticatedFetch.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">ALL HTTP calls via `@spaarke/auth.authenticatedFetch`. NO raw `fetch`. NO manual `Authorization` headers.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Lives in `@spaarke/ui-components/services/` per shared library home.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React-16-safe (this file has no React deps so trivially safe).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">R1 = READ-ONLY. There's no write contract on `IDataverseClient` so this is a non-issue for the 5 methods. Document the limitation in JSDoc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ProblemDetails responses → typed errors: `BffNotFoundError` (404), `BffForbiddenError` (403), `BffBadRequestError` (400), `BffServerError` (5xx).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`bffBaseUrl` configurable; defaults to `process.env.SPAARKE_BFF_URL` or `window.SPAARKE_BFF_URL` if available.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-pcf-platform-libraries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/auth.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/obo-flow.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/oauth-scopes.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
