      <file>docs/guides/auth-deployment-setup.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-datagrid-framework-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="authenticatedFetch usage" location="src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl.tsx">Existing canonical usage pattern for `@spaarke/auth.authenticatedFetch`.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `IDataverseClient.ts` (task 001) for the 5 method signatures.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `BffDataverseClient.ts` with constructor `(options: { bffBaseUrl?: string })`; resolve `bffBaseUrl` from options → `window.SPAARKE_BFF_URL` → `process.env.SPAARKE_BFF_URL` → throw if none.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement each method routing to BFF endpoint:
      - `retrieveSavedQuery(id)` → `GET /api/dataverse/savedquery/{id}`
      - `retrieveSavedQueriesForEntity(entity)` → `GET /api/dataverse/savedqueries/{entity}`
      - `retrieveEntityMetadata(entity)` → `GET /api/dataverse/metadata/{entity}`
      - `retrieveMultipleRecords(entity, fetchXml)` → `POST /api/dataverse/fetch`
      - `retrieveRecord(entity, id, columnSet)` → `GET /api/dataverse/record/{entity}/{id}?$select=...`
    </step>
    <step order="4">Implement ProblemDetails error unwrap helper: on non-2xx response, parse `{ type, title, status, detail }` and throw typed error.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `src/index.ts` barrel export.</step>
    <step order="6">Author Jest tests with mocked `authenticatedFetch` (via Jest mock or msw); test happy path for each method, 404/403/400 error mapping, missing `bffBaseUrl` error.</step>
    <step order="7">Build (`npm run build`); verify zero TypeScript errors. Run tests (`npm test`); verify pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX (015 ✅).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build + test</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Author code + tests</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/BffDataverseClient.ts</output>
    <output type="test">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/tests/services/BffDataverseClient.test.ts</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `BffDataverseClient` and `XrmDataverseClient`, when both implement `IDataverseClient`, then consumer swap requires zero code change.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `authenticatedFetch` mock returning 403 ProblemDetails, when method called, then `BffForbiddenError` is thrown.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `bffBaseUrl` unset (no options + no env + no window), when constructor called, then clear error thrown.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `npm run build`, when run, then zero TypeScript errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given grep for `fetch(` (raw fetch) in `BffDataverseClient.ts`, when run, then zero matches.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The 5 methods are 1:1 with the 5 BFF endpoints. Keep this client thin — no caching at this layer (server caches via IDistributedCache). The ProblemDetails error unwrap is the key affordance for consumers; without typed errors, consumers can't differentiate "not found" from "no privilege" from "bad request" without parsing strings.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Verify all 5 endpoints integrated + tests pass + grep for raw `fetch(` returns zero before marking complete.</protocol>
